One of the famous faces at the Commission of Inquiry into State Capture, advocate Vincent Maleka (SC) was lucky to escape unharmed when armed robbers pounced on him at his Randburg home in Joburg early on Monday morning. The tsotsis made off with Maleka's laptop, camera, cash, two bank cards and cellphones worth R50,000. TO READ MORE ON THIS STORY GET A COPY OF TODAY'S SUNDAY WORLD